data.meta_description: Jun 14, 2023 - Felton Covered Bridge County Park features the historic covered bridge that stood as the only entry to Felton for 45 years. Dating back to 1892-93, the Felton covered bridge is believed to be the tallest covered bridge in the country. Now a pedestrian bridge that connects to a park, the Felton Covered Bridge is a charming location for intimate ceremonies. Couples are welcome to choose to have the bridge as a picturesque backdrop or as the setting for their ceremony. See more ideas about county park, pedestrian bridge, covered bridges.
